WEBVTT

00:01.406 --> 00:04.938
- Graham: Welcome to "Everlasting."
- [Cheers and applause]

00:05.244 --> 00:07.673
- Why'd you come back?
- I wanted to see you.

00:08.863 --> 00:10.435
Maybe we should postpone the wedding.

00:10.435 --> 00:13.002
- This is about Rachel.
- Maybe.

00:13.968 --> 00:16.768
- Mary's a freaking robot.
- I'm surprised she can feel <i>anything</i>

00:16.769 --> 00:19.192
with all the mood stabilizers she's on.

00:23.261 --> 00:27.763
My doctor told me never
to mix this with this,

00:27.765 --> 00:30.783
but I feel amazing.

00:30.785 --> 00:32.772
- Mm.
- Mary: <i>So excited.</i>

00:32.773 --> 00:35.973
<i>I get to see my little girl,
and she gets to meet Adam.</i>

00:35.999 --> 00:36.773
My sister.

00:36.774 --> 00:40.025
Who let Shia talk me
into this family playdate?

00:40.027 --> 00:41.894
She's got an ex-husband, right?

00:41.895 --> 00:44.806
He hit her. He basically, you
know, broke Lily Belle's arms.

00:44.806 --> 00:46.582
We could bring him in.

00:46.584 --> 00:49.362
I mean, it could help Mary get
a little bit of closure, I guess.

00:49.362 --> 00:51.137
- Someone please make him leave.
- Kirk: It's not right, Mary. I just...

00:51.138 --> 00:53.839
- Hold on, mate.
- Shut up! You know what?

00:54.361 --> 00:57.758
Something's wrong. It's Mary.
Somehow, she got on the roof.

00:57.852 --> 00:59.178
Give me your hand right now.

00:59.180 --> 01:00.986
Mary! Wait!

01:08.875 --> 01:11.866
Rachel... Rach.

01:12.952 --> 01:14.819
I had her hand.

01:14.841 --> 01:17.643
- Hey.
- I had her.

01:17.705 --> 01:19.044
It's okay.

01:19.070 --> 01:21.212
It's okay. Hey.

01:21.900 --> 01:23.978
Hey, it's gonna be all right.

01:24.239 --> 01:25.707
Come on.

01:25.937 --> 01:27.404
Let's go.

01:28.343 --> 01:31.756
Sync & corrections by <font color="#d61dfc">PetaG</font>
- www.addic7ed.com -

01:31.757 --> 01:32.928
Jay: Oh, my God. What happened?

01:32.928 --> 01:35.365
It's all right. Get those girls
to a room and make them stay there,

01:35.365 --> 01:37.504
and tell them they cannot
speak to anybody but Chet or me.

01:37.504 --> 01:38.595
- What do we tell them?
- The truth, all right?

01:38.595 --> 01:40.011
You don't know jack. Go.

01:40.396 --> 01:41.895
Shia, did you hear me?

01:41.896 --> 01:43.376
- Um, Mary,
- Shia,

01:43.392 --> 01:45.321
- what...
- get those girls out of here now.

01:47.128 --> 01:49.819
- Where are we going?
- Jay: Faster, faster. Come on, girls.

01:49.819 --> 01:51.498
Is somebody going to
tell us what's going on?

01:51.498 --> 01:53.041
They haven't told us for eight weeks,

01:53.042 --> 01:53.982
- why start now?
- Hey!

01:53.984 --> 01:55.402
- [Sirens wailing in distance]
- Yeah, come on, Shia, just say.

01:55.403 --> 01:58.671
- What's up with the sirens?
- I'm not really sure. Sorry.

01:58.672 --> 02:01.219
- Faith: Come on. You know. You work here.
- Look at her... she's lying.

02:01.219 --> 02:03.552
You know what, ladies? Let's just...
let's just keep it moving, all right?

02:03.552 --> 02:04.909
Adam: What the hell is going on?

02:04.911 --> 02:07.085
Everything's all right. Just
go back to your room, Adam.

02:07.085 --> 02:08.924
- Rachel, are you okay? What happened?
- She's gonna be fine.

02:08.924 --> 02:09.783
Over here!

02:09.785 --> 02:11.362
Madison: Quinn just wants
everyone in their room.

02:11.362 --> 02:12.986
No, not until somebody explains
to me what the hell is...

02:12.986 --> 02:15.503
[Voice breaking] Adam, please stop, okay?

02:15.505 --> 02:16.805
[Wailing sirens continue]

02:18.542 --> 02:19.747
Okay, girls, hurry it up, please.

02:19.748 --> 02:21.999
Everyone in. Come on. Come on.

02:21.999 --> 02:23.402
- Okay.
- Thank you.

02:23.402 --> 02:25.347
Hey, can we get, um, a few...

02:25.578 --> 02:28.856
There's a cop car and
an ambulance out there.

02:29.643 --> 02:32.614
When my dad died, they called
an ambulance for no reason.

02:32.614 --> 02:34.313
It was... It was all for show.

02:34.313 --> 02:36.441
This is obviously a stunt.

02:36.544 --> 02:38.766
Come here. Come here. Are you okay?

02:39.191 --> 02:40.612
Just look at me, all right?

02:40.614 --> 02:42.270
She's dead, isn't she?

02:42.313 --> 02:45.738
Listen, we are so
supremely screwed right now.

02:45.825 --> 02:47.787
I need you to stay strong, okay?

02:47.787 --> 02:49.120
What happened?

02:49.122 --> 02:53.736
Th-The whole thing with
Kirk... this is on us.

02:53.736 --> 02:55.974
- This is our fault.
- Okay, okay.

02:55.974 --> 02:57.930
Come here, come here.

02:58.765 --> 03:01.349
[Sighs, sniffles]

03:01.351 --> 03:03.475
- Anyone seen Mary?
- Uh-uh.

03:03.475 --> 03:05.750
- No.
- Maybe something's wrong with her.

03:05.750 --> 03:08.844
I bet she's just with Adam.
I mean, she just won the date.

03:08.845 --> 03:11.609
They probably want us sitting around
dissing her 'cause we're jealous.

03:11.609 --> 03:14.987
Typical, it's all made up. 100% delusional.

03:14.987 --> 03:18.073
No, I don't know. This...
this seems real to me.

03:18.073 --> 03:20.607
- It always <i>looks</i> real.
- This is different.

03:20.607 --> 03:22.487
There are... there are no cameras there.

03:22.489 --> 03:25.228
- They're... they're not shooting it.
- [Police radio chatter]

03:25.610 --> 03:28.236
You guys, she's right.
There's no cameras out there.

03:28.775 --> 03:30.161
Or in here.

03:34.301 --> 03:36.835
- Oh, okay. Here we go.
- [Computer chimes]

03:36.837 --> 03:39.091
Now, remember, it's the
network, so keep it upbeat,

03:39.091 --> 03:40.672
but also, somebody died.

03:40.674 --> 03:42.424
- Yeah, okay.
- Okay.

03:42.426 --> 03:44.131
- [Ringing]
- Oh, God.

03:44.478 --> 03:45.678
What?

03:46.100 --> 03:47.733
Two deaths in one season.

03:47.734 --> 03:49.848
First Anna's dad, and now this.

03:49.850 --> 03:51.599
- So?
- It's out there.

03:51.949 --> 03:53.596
Okay, here we go. Hey, Brad.

03:53.597 --> 03:54.887
Chet: Sorry to get you up.

03:54.888 --> 03:57.355
<i>What the hell's going on? It's 2:00 A.M.</i>

03:57.357 --> 03:59.691
Uh, a little bit of a situation here.

03:59.693 --> 04:05.323
Uh, uh, one of our c-cast
members passed away... Mary.

04:06.268 --> 04:09.463
<i>Oh, well, oh, my God, I'm... I'm so sorry.</i>

04:09.463 --> 04:11.095
<i>She... she was a black girl, right?</i>

04:11.095 --> 04:13.932
No. The mom.

04:14.207 --> 04:16.779
[Indistinct conversation]

04:16.779 --> 04:18.524
[Police radio chatter]

04:18.524 --> 04:20.043
[Sighs]

04:20.877 --> 04:22.795
Hey, Rachel, uh, I got to talk to you.

04:22.795 --> 04:24.090
Yeah, what is it, Shia?

04:24.091 --> 04:26.104
Look, it's just Mary...
I don't know what to think.

04:26.104 --> 04:28.740
I know, sweetie, we're all
asking ourselves the same thing.

04:28.740 --> 04:31.523
No, no, I got to talk this
through, and you got to listen.

04:31.525 --> 04:33.141
Rachel Goldberg?

04:33.143 --> 04:34.476
Yes.

04:34.478 --> 04:36.227
I need to get a statement.

04:36.820 --> 04:38.275
All right.

04:40.901 --> 04:43.669
Brad: <i>I'm gonna call Legal.
We'll deal with the family.</i>

04:43.669 --> 04:47.101
<i>You let your people know, but I want to
zip this thing up airtight, all right?</i>

04:47.101 --> 04:48.262
<i>That means no Twitter</i>

04:48.263 --> 04:50.436
<i>- and no Instagram pics.</i>
- Got it.

04:50.436 --> 04:52.413
<i>I'll be up there on the
first flight in the morning,</i>

04:52.413 --> 04:54.548
<i>so you send the crew
home but hold the cast.</i>

04:54.548 --> 04:57.045
<i>And I do not want a single frame shot</i>

04:57.045 --> 04:58.668
<i>until we are back up, understood?</i>

04:58.668 --> 05:02.754
Okay. Brad, about how long
are we talking about here?

05:02.756 --> 05:06.128
<i>A week, a month... no
idea, and I won't know</i>

05:06.128 --> 05:08.560
<i>until we get Legal up there
and see what's happening.</i>

05:08.562 --> 05:10.261
- Uh-huh.
- Right, of... of course,

05:10.263 --> 05:12.111
but we don't want the cast

05:12.112 --> 05:13.775
- to stew on this.
<i>- Forget it, Quinn,</i>

05:13.775 --> 05:14.983
<i>okay? You're shut down.</i>

05:14.985 --> 05:17.274
<i>You hear me? All right.</i>

05:17.274 --> 05:18.853
<i>I'll see you tomorrow.</i>

05:18.855 --> 05:20.772
[Computer chimes]

05:21.325 --> 05:22.941
[Sighs]

05:22.943 --> 05:25.076
[Sighs]

05:28.782 --> 05:31.115
Woman: You have 20 minutes
to break it down now.

05:31.117 --> 05:32.517
[Electricity hums]

05:36.923 --> 05:38.702
You can't hold me here like a prisoner.

05:38.702 --> 05:41.659
I'm not Edward Snowden.
This is a game show.

05:41.659 --> 05:42.909
You love this, don't you? You

05:42.910 --> 05:45.096
- really love it.
- I got it. Thanks.

05:45.843 --> 05:47.497
What the hell is going on?

05:47.497 --> 05:49.968
- I... I do not like being lied to.
- Nobody's lying to you.

05:49.970 --> 05:51.544
We're just trying to
figure out what happened,

05:51.544 --> 05:54.034
and until we do, we just
need everybody to stay...

05:54.034 --> 05:56.774
- No, don't try to spin me.
- Mary killed herself.

05:57.361 --> 06:00.171
She seem... I mean, she was happy. I...

06:00.247 --> 06:02.254
Even after Kirk came, she seemed fine. I...

06:02.255 --> 06:04.870
I know. We talked, I
thought I had her, but...

06:06.313 --> 06:07.515
You know, I'm okay.

06:07.516 --> 06:09.893
I... I just have to try and stay focused,

06:09.894 --> 06:11.216
- so...
- Yeah.

06:11.217 --> 06:12.949
It would be really great if you could just

06:12.949 --> 06:14.909
talk to the rest of the cast, the girls.

06:15.738 --> 06:17.605
Me? No, no. I don't think that would...

06:17.605 --> 06:20.598
I really think it needs to come from
somebody that they know and trust.

06:20.964 --> 06:24.135
That's insane. I'm not a grief
counselor, for God's sake.

06:24.135 --> 06:26.716
I'm... I'm English.

06:26.716 --> 06:28.855
Look, you've just been there
for them for so many things,

06:28.855 --> 06:31.792
you know, like Anna's dad,
that whole thing with Faith,

06:31.792 --> 06:34.835
and you took a hit for Mary,
literally. That means something.

06:34.836 --> 06:36.342
Yeah, but, I mean, those things weren't...

06:36.342 --> 06:39.858
this is... I mean, she's... she's dead.

06:39.858 --> 06:41.387
I don't know what to do about that,

06:41.387 --> 06:43.216
and I certainly don't know what to say.

06:44.066 --> 06:45.773
Just tell them the truth.

06:47.231 --> 06:49.018
[Door opens]

06:56.086 --> 06:58.252
- Rachel: Dude, Shia.
- Rachel.

06:58.252 --> 06:59.087
- This is... This is bad.
- I know.

06:59.089 --> 07:00.705
- What happened's so bad.
- I... I know.

07:00.707 --> 07:02.206
- This is on me, okay?
- I know that.

07:02.208 --> 07:04.634
- I called Kirk. I got it.
- No, no, no, no.

07:04.634 --> 07:08.046
Mary... Mary was my girl, and I, um...

07:08.253 --> 07:09.462
You what?

07:09.609 --> 07:12.216
Her... her meds. They were
making her like a zombie.

07:12.397 --> 07:13.939
Dude, she wasn't a zombie yesterday.

07:13.939 --> 07:15.803
She was hyper. She was all over the place.

07:15.805 --> 07:18.034
Because... that's 'cause
she went off her meds.

07:18.034 --> 07:20.369
- Shia, did she tell you that?
- I was trying to help her.

07:20.369 --> 07:22.790
She was never gonna win if
she stayed on those things.

07:23.089 --> 07:26.599
Okay, so did you ask her to
get off of her medication?

07:26.599 --> 07:28.024
Is that what you're saying?

07:28.710 --> 07:31.069
I... I swapped out a few of her pills.

07:31.607 --> 07:33.278
You what?

07:34.740 --> 07:37.145
No, look, it was just for a couple of days.

07:37.145 --> 07:39.090
You saw her. She came alive on camera.

07:39.090 --> 07:41.182
I got her off the
sidelines and into the game.

07:41.182 --> 07:43.420
- I delivered a win.
- No, you didn't. You delivered a body.

07:43.420 --> 07:44.920
- I only did what you would've done.
- I would have never

07:44.921 --> 07:45.820
done something like that.

07:45.821 --> 07:48.083
That's the problem with you,
Shia. You always cross the line.

07:48.084 --> 07:50.251
Don't give me that. You and
Quinn don't <i>have</i> a line,

07:50.252 --> 07:51.783
- and you know it.
- Are you kidding me? Of course we do.

07:51.784 --> 07:53.624
We'd never put somebody's life at risk.

07:53.624 --> 07:54.989
You called Kirk.

07:54.990 --> 07:58.930
- You even said it was your call.
- Kirk didn't kill her, you did.

08:00.577 --> 08:02.929
- I got to get out of here.
- No.

08:02.930 --> 08:04.786
No, this place is on lockdown,

08:04.786 --> 08:06.104
and I am not gonna lie for you.

08:06.106 --> 08:08.439
You don't have to lie,
just don't say anything.

08:08.441 --> 08:11.042
You need to call Quinn.
You need to tell the police.

08:11.044 --> 08:12.430
The whole show could go down.

08:12.431 --> 08:15.360
- We could all go to jail.
- We really don't have a choice, Shia.

08:16.658 --> 08:17.988
My God.

08:18.120 --> 08:20.034
Look, what's gonna happen to us?

08:24.666 --> 08:29.603
[Birds chirping]

08:29.605 --> 08:33.106
[Chatter]

08:39.092 --> 08:41.948
Quinn, can I... can I talk to you?

08:41.950 --> 08:43.150
Not now.

08:43.150 --> 08:45.055
Mm, I wouldn't wait.

08:47.289 --> 08:48.872
Come on.

08:55.831 --> 08:58.298
Uh, hi, everyone. Uh...

08:59.933 --> 09:02.720
Hey sorry, I know this has
been a really long night.

09:02.721 --> 09:08.111
Um, and, uh, I don't really
know how to say this...

09:09.676 --> 09:14.612
Uh, one of our own, Mary...
she took her own life.

09:14.612 --> 09:16.857
- [Woman gasps]
- Oh, no.

09:16.857 --> 09:19.134
So, I can imagine we're all
in a lot of shock right now,

09:19.134 --> 09:24.004
and, uh, this is just a very, very sad day.

09:24.390 --> 09:27.994
[Sobs]

09:28.622 --> 09:30.914
Uh, thank you. Thank you, Adam.

09:30.916 --> 09:33.911
You are very kind.

09:33.911 --> 09:37.525
Uh, we are going to stop shooting

09:37.943 --> 09:40.103
for a little while, ladies.

09:40.234 --> 09:45.275
Uh, Dr. Wagerstein is
available if you need her.

09:45.462 --> 09:50.233
We're a family, and we are going
to get through this together.

09:50.653 --> 09:52.436
[Indistinct conversations]

09:52.632 --> 09:54.716
I just feel so terrible.

09:55.004 --> 09:57.997
I thought that she was
being selfish yesterday,

09:57.997 --> 10:00.322
but... you know,
something was really wrong,

10:00.322 --> 10:02.195
and I didn't... I didn't realize.

10:02.197 --> 10:06.435
- I can't believe it. I can't. Why?
- Who knows?

10:06.436 --> 10:09.439
Sometimes, you just never know
what's going on with people.

10:10.144 --> 10:11.855
You didn't even like her.

10:12.285 --> 10:14.621
You don't even seem torn up about it.

10:14.636 --> 10:16.051
What are you talking about?

10:16.051 --> 10:18.185
You're not even crying.

10:18.671 --> 10:21.205
What are you, just, like, happy

10:21.270 --> 10:23.133
that there's less competition?

10:23.135 --> 10:26.768
Maya, I've seen more death in my
life than I care to think about.

10:27.002 --> 10:30.390
I've learned to deal with
it in my own way, okay?

10:30.980 --> 10:36.341
Hey, everyone, where I'm from,
we always pray on a hard time.

10:36.643 --> 10:39.351
And I thought that some of y'all
would like to join me in a prayer.

10:39.351 --> 10:40.993
Grab hands, okay?

10:43.097 --> 10:47.630
Dear Lord, today we lost a beautiful soul

10:48.433 --> 10:50.627
who always shined so bright.

10:51.002 --> 10:53.912
Please accept her into your glory

10:53.912 --> 10:55.318
and protect her little one,

10:55.319 --> 10:57.049
- This is for you.
- Lily Belle, from harm.

10:57.180 --> 10:59.936
Quinn: Rachel, get in here. I need you now.

11:00.005 --> 11:02.445
We could be talking murder charges.

11:03.007 --> 11:05.203
[Voice breaking] I want to go home.

11:06.360 --> 11:10.156
I... I think I need a lawyer.

11:10.897 --> 11:13.933
No, um, no...

11:15.352 --> 11:17.938
no lawyers, all right?

11:17.939 --> 11:20.926
You are in no condition to go home.

11:21.615 --> 11:24.444
I'm gonna fix this for you, okay?

11:25.258 --> 11:27.114
But you got to trust me.

11:28.369 --> 11:30.166
Now get yourself cleaned up.

11:30.682 --> 11:32.180
Use my bathroom.

11:37.159 --> 11:40.176
[Dialing]

11:40.178 --> 11:42.012
[Ringing]

11:42.014 --> 11:45.879
Jay, get a car. Now.

11:46.968 --> 11:48.674
- Hey, Brad.
- Hey.

11:48.674 --> 11:50.463
- Glad you're here.
- Yeah.

11:50.714 --> 11:52.338
Despite the circumstances.

11:52.339 --> 11:55.442
No, you're just going along
one day, and then... this.

11:55.442 --> 11:59.029
You remember Sandy, our general
counsel, and Judith from Legal.

11:59.570 --> 12:00.851
Hi.

12:00.852 --> 12:02.457
Rachel: We have to call
the police, I mean, I know

12:02.458 --> 12:04.744
that Shia's gonna get in trouble.
We're all gonna get in trouble,

12:04.744 --> 12:07.405
- but this is crazy serious.
- Mary took her own life...

12:07.567 --> 12:09.262
end of story.

12:11.342 --> 12:13.434
No, no. Quinn, we have to

12:13.435 --> 12:15.991
- take responsibility. Yes, we do have to.
- No, we don't <i>have to</i> do anything.

12:15.992 --> 12:18.043
- Shia switched out her meds, now Mary...
- Mary killed herself.

12:18.044 --> 12:19.643
- It is our responsibility.
- Okay,

12:19.644 --> 12:21.542
you want to turn this into a homicide?

12:21.705 --> 12:23.719
This show has zero chance of coming back.

12:23.719 --> 12:25.962
- It dies along with Mary.
- Who... who gives a shit about a TV show?

12:25.962 --> 12:28.686
- We're talking about somebody's life here.
- Well, I am talking about

12:28.687 --> 12:33.601
more than one life... 170 people will
lose their jobs if this show goes down.

12:33.601 --> 12:36.593
Eddie and Frank will have to
pull their kids out of college.

12:36.593 --> 12:39.837
And why? Because we made Mary jump?

12:40.018 --> 12:43.806
No. What about the millions of
other people who take those pills?

12:43.806 --> 12:45.604
Nobody skips a couple of days

12:45.604 --> 12:46.887
- and they don't live.
- Quinn, that's not

12:46.887 --> 12:49.229
- the same thing. It's totally different.
- Listen, come on, all right. Listen to me,

12:49.229 --> 12:54.397
the truth is we are never going
to know why she took her life...

12:54.397 --> 12:57.563
- the pills, Kirk, the voices in her head.
- I don't even think that

12:57.563 --> 12:59.355
- it's for us to decide something...
- You just wanna

12:59.355 --> 13:01.781
clear your conscience to
make yourself feel better,

13:01.781 --> 13:04.562
but that comes at a very high price.

13:05.925 --> 13:08.294
So before you go all
Jiminy Cricket on everyone,

13:08.294 --> 13:09.883
- [Door opens]
- Think about that.

13:10.186 --> 13:13.129
Hi, um, sorry. The
network lawyers are here,

13:13.129 --> 13:14.329
and they want to see you.

13:15.072 --> 13:16.566
I'll be right there.

13:17.467 --> 13:19.674
Actually, they want to see both of you.

13:21.451 --> 13:24.228
Ms. Goldberg, you contacted Mr. Newhouse

13:24.228 --> 13:27.230
and invited him to visit
his ex-wife on the show.

13:27.230 --> 13:29.349
- Yes.
- And at that time, were you aware

13:29.349 --> 13:31.989
that Mr. Newhouse had a history
of violence toward his family?

