28:33.463 --> 28:37.298
[Rachel sighs]

28:40.913 --> 28:44.004
I mean, is that how it works here?
You got the inmates running the asylum?

28:44.005 --> 28:45.421
Quinn's not an inmate.

28:45.422 --> 28:47.172
Okay, she gave you a hit show

28:47.173 --> 28:49.156
and a corner office next to Gary.

28:49.175 --> 28:50.575
Yeah, she also gave me

28:50.576 --> 28:52.872
a potential wrongful-death lawsuit.

28:52.873 --> 28:54.229
Why don't you just give Quinn a chance?

28:54.230 --> 28:56.516
- She's only the best at what she does.
- It doesn't matter because

28:56.517 --> 28:57.832
you have got nothing

28:57.833 --> 29:00.336
- that is gonna save this show.
- Oh, come on, Brad.

29:00.337 --> 29:02.437
It's not just <i>her</i>
job on the line, all right?

29:02.438 --> 29:05.228
You will be named in any lawsuit
against this show, as well,

29:05.229 --> 29:06.931
so if I were you, I'd lawyer up, bub.

29:06.932 --> 29:08.682
Because the shit's hit the fan.

29:08.683 --> 29:12.048
Uh, Chet, I found something.

29:12.396 --> 29:17.235
Mary... she, um... she left a note.

29:22.747 --> 29:26.652
[Indistinct conversations,
camera shutter clicks]

29:26.653 --> 29:28.570
- We are here live...
- There they are.

29:28.572 --> 29:30.822
- There they are.
- [Indistinct shouting]

29:30.824 --> 29:32.124
Roll down the window!

29:32.126 --> 29:34.073
All right, step back, everybody.

29:34.073 --> 29:36.328
Hey, hey, no, no, no. Don't go past here.

29:38.415 --> 29:41.750
[Brakes squeal]

29:41.752 --> 29:43.218
[Indistinct conversations]

29:45.839 --> 29:48.344
Louise, thanks for coming.

29:53.814 --> 29:55.046
My poor sister.

29:55.048 --> 29:57.816
I can't believe it. [Sniffles]

30:02.047 --> 30:03.250
You're right.

30:04.401 --> 30:06.853
We really need to read this on camera.

30:06.854 --> 30:09.278
I mean, if it's something that
you would be comfortable with,

30:09.278 --> 30:12.656
it would certainly help paint
the show in a better light,

30:12.657 --> 30:15.294
and it would be so good for Mary, too.

30:15.295 --> 30:16.877
It's not just about Mary.

30:17.865 --> 30:22.084
Kirk's power-bitch
lawyer is already angling

30:22.085 --> 30:23.844
to get Lily Belle away from me.

30:24.094 --> 30:26.427
I'll be damned if I let that happen.

30:26.428 --> 30:29.407
Yeah, okay, well, you know, I
can, uh, get the letter to Graham,

30:29.408 --> 30:31.573
make sure that he reads
it on camera tonight.

30:32.052 --> 30:34.986
No. I want to read it.

30:35.889 --> 30:37.856
Me, my tears.

30:38.896 --> 30:40.402
Okay.

30:44.777 --> 30:46.026
[Indistinct conversations]

30:46.027 --> 30:47.357
Man: And we're back.

30:47.587 --> 30:49.137
[Bell rings]

30:50.540 --> 30:52.240
So, as soon as he steps off his mark,

30:52.241 --> 30:55.242
you're just gonna step right in
and look right at the camera...

30:55.243 --> 30:57.398
- [Sighs]
- ... Okay.

30:57.739 --> 31:00.560
- All right, we're ready.
- Camera's rolling.

31:01.916 --> 31:04.564
Speed and action.

31:05.180 --> 31:07.769
This week, the "Everlasting" family

31:07.770 --> 31:11.912
tragically lost one of
its own... Mary Newhouse.

31:13.201 --> 31:16.229
Her sad decision to end her
life has left all of us here

31:16.229 --> 31:19.348
with one aching question... why?

31:20.160 --> 31:22.532
<i>What was Mary thinking in her final hour?</i>

31:22.937 --> 31:24.487
We thought we'd never know.

31:24.488 --> 31:26.199
And then a staff member found something

31:26.200 --> 31:29.371
that Mary had left in her
room... her child's Teddy bear.

31:29.845 --> 31:33.283
And inside was a note that Mary
left specifically for her daughter.

31:33.607 --> 31:37.731
And here to share it with
us, her sister, Louise.

31:38.971 --> 31:40.253
Louise.

31:40.838 --> 31:42.948
- Louise: Um. [Clears throat]
- [Paper rustles]

31:42.948 --> 31:45.373
- [Sniffles]
- [Paper continues to rustle]

31:45.374 --> 31:46.841
"Darling girl,

31:48.369 --> 31:52.616
<i>from the first time I held
you to our final hug goodbye,</i>

31:53.385 --> 31:56.061
<i>you have been my greatest joy.</i>

31:56.537 --> 31:59.350
You made this world shine for me.

31:59.890 --> 32:03.032
If only I could have done the same for you.

32:03.554 --> 32:07.139
Getting to know Adam over
the last couple of weeks

32:07.140 --> 32:11.237
has given me so much hope and happiness."

32:13.005 --> 32:16.873
"For the first time in
years, I felt confident enough

32:16.873 --> 32:19.945
to stop counting on
medication to keep me afloat

32:19.946 --> 32:22.863
and dull the pain of everyday life."

32:25.549 --> 32:32.521
"Our day on "Everlasting" was
magical, a dream come true.

32:34.074 --> 32:37.047
But I never should have
invited your father."

32:38.752 --> 32:41.336
"I hoped you could have
seen him someplace safe,

32:41.337 --> 32:42.803
see that he loves you.

32:43.150 --> 32:46.669
Baby, now I know for sure
that as long as I'm alive,

32:47.001 --> 32:51.290
your daddy will try and
hurt me and anyone I love."

32:54.315 --> 32:57.536
[Voice breaking] "That's why
I need to go away, baby girl.

32:58.809 --> 33:02.532
I'm safe now, and you are free.

33:03.453 --> 33:06.488
Goodbye, my little bunny.

33:07.374 --> 33:09.347
Mama loves you."

33:09.348 --> 33:10.916
Let's go to the shot of Mary.

33:11.962 --> 33:13.428
Woman: Cut away.

33:13.430 --> 33:15.213
- Queue it up.
- Hold.

33:19.003 --> 33:20.393
And cut.

33:20.394 --> 33:21.977
- [Bell rings]
- Man: That's a wrap, everybody.

33:21.978 --> 33:25.196
- [Sobbing]
- That was amazing.

33:25.784 --> 33:29.277
Amazing job with Mary's words.
You really did a great job.

33:29.354 --> 33:30.812
- Thanks.
- Mm.

33:31.266 --> 33:32.814
Nice job on the note.

33:32.816 --> 33:35.533
I almost believed it was real.

33:38.139 --> 33:41.888
- Louise, I don't even know what to...
- Don't. It was smart.

33:41.888 --> 33:43.253
It had to be done.

33:43.254 --> 33:44.711
You okay with this?

33:45.579 --> 33:48.246
[Sniffles] Absolutely.

33:48.716 --> 33:52.438
Whatever it takes to keep Lily
Belle away from that monster.

34:10.882 --> 34:14.050
What did Quinn say when she
told you to bring me back here?

34:14.052 --> 34:15.746
Look, I just want to know
what I'm walking into.

34:15.746 --> 34:18.107
Just that she wanted to see you.

34:18.324 --> 34:20.040
Okay, just trust her on this.

34:20.040 --> 34:21.670
Yeah, I'm not trusting anyone right now.

34:21.670 --> 34:23.808
[Chuckles] Look, I know
you're probably thinking

34:23.808 --> 34:25.504
that I'm just like some super crappy friend

34:25.504 --> 34:27.751
for not letting you tell me
about your whole situation,

34:27.752 --> 34:29.554
- but I...
- Yeah, that's exactly what I think,

34:29.554 --> 34:32.091
- and you know I'm right.
- No, you're not.

34:32.092 --> 34:35.679
You wanted to tell me a
secret, and secrets, Shia,

34:35.681 --> 34:39.149
like <i>real</i> secrets,
do not make people closer.

34:40.299 --> 34:44.878
But you and I... we're still good.

34:46.766 --> 34:48.415
Come on.

34:48.879 --> 34:53.371
Fantastic job... just chills,
just so emotional, you know.

34:53.371 --> 34:55.033
It... it's gonna be an incredible episode.

34:55.033 --> 34:58.232
- Hey, we'll dedicate it to Mary.
- Perfect.

34:58.232 --> 35:00.841
By the way, the lawyers
say that that letter...

35:00.842 --> 35:02.266
it's really gonna help us.

35:02.267 --> 35:04.420
So, you know, you delivered, my friend.

35:04.421 --> 35:06.851
- Team effort, my brother. Thank you.
- [Chuckles]

35:08.574 --> 35:11.574
Look, Quinn, I know
that we said some things,

35:11.576 --> 35:14.063
but when you throw down
hard, you bounce back high.

35:14.064 --> 35:16.281
And we're gonna be on top again soon.

35:16.282 --> 35:18.659
Well, it's all about the show. I know.

35:18.660 --> 35:19.930
So, we'll talk tomorrow.

35:19.930 --> 35:21.348
- All right.
- Have a safe flight.

35:21.349 --> 35:23.005
- Thank you.
- Okay.

35:25.577 --> 35:28.277
That bitch goes up against
me again, she's fired.

35:28.278 --> 35:29.971
- Won't happen. I wouldn't worry about it.
- [Engine turns over]

35:29.972 --> 35:33.350
- Okay.
- Bye. Safe flight.

35:33.350 --> 35:35.298
- Thanks.
- [Car door opens, closes]

35:35.941 --> 35:37.141
Bye.

35:38.462 --> 35:41.254
Home slice, where the hell you guys been?

35:41.255 --> 35:43.244
Go ahead, okay? I'll catch up, all right.

35:45.089 --> 35:47.362
Quinn wanted me to keep an eye on her.

35:48.030 --> 35:50.459
But, hey, I heard we're back on the air.

35:50.459 --> 35:52.585
I have got primo

35:52.586 --> 35:54.750
- effing hash, let's celebrate.
- No, no, I can't. I can't.

35:54.750 --> 35:57.400
I got to make a... phone call.

35:58.498 --> 36:00.502
[Sighs]

36:06.011 --> 36:07.331
You should go get some sleep.

36:07.331 --> 36:09.165
- Mm?
- You look like crap.

36:09.521 --> 36:13.429
Nothing a couple shots of
tequila can't fix... or bottles.

36:13.430 --> 36:17.367
Ah, look who's back. Did
you get some rest, sunshine?

36:17.368 --> 36:18.807
Well what was that about?

36:18.807 --> 36:20.484
You literally held me prisoner.

36:20.485 --> 36:24.097
You suck at poker, Shia,
so I didn't want to put you

36:24.099 --> 36:26.221
in the position of having to bluff.

36:26.485 --> 36:29.565
Listen, the police... they
ruled Mary's death a suicide,

36:29.566 --> 36:32.322
so there's not gonna be any more questions.

36:32.323 --> 36:33.548
Shia: Really?

36:33.549 --> 36:36.581
Is that all you care
about? Getting away with it?

36:36.582 --> 36:38.341
Don't either of you feel guilty?

36:38.342 --> 36:40.994
- Those girls know what they signed on for.
- No, they don't.

36:41.528 --> 36:43.720
They have no idea... the crap we pull.

36:43.721 --> 36:47.890
Please, it is no worse than what
happens to them in real life.

36:47.891 --> 36:53.106
Maybe you should go see a priest
or a shrink... guru, perhaps.

36:53.107 --> 36:54.307
What do you do?

36:54.308 --> 36:57.712
- I work.
- Okay, then... then put me back to work.

36:58.216 --> 37:00.051
You don't have any girls left.

37:00.052 --> 37:01.852
- But Maya...
- Quit.

37:01.853 --> 37:04.008
So just go home.

37:05.690 --> 37:07.140
And be grateful that

37:07.142 --> 37:09.660
that's where you're going instead of jail.

37:12.854 --> 37:14.070
[Door closes]

37:14.071 --> 37:16.016
All right, well, I'm out.

37:16.017 --> 37:19.278
- [Sighs]
- Uh, look, I know that this

37:19.279 --> 37:23.434
has been a lot, so if
you ever need to talk...

37:26.104 --> 37:27.635
Thanks.

37:28.258 --> 37:30.118
You know we're never
talking about this again.

37:30.119 --> 37:31.738
Probably not.

37:34.621 --> 37:38.078
♪ Take me home, tend me ♪

37:38.366 --> 37:40.674
♪ Babe, you let me down easy ♪

37:40.675 --> 37:42.425
- You got everything?
- I'm good.

37:42.427 --> 37:46.155
♪ For I have grown weary on my own ♪

37:50.104 --> 37:56.659
♪ Oh, all alone, I wither and I burst ♪

37:56.660 --> 38:00.160
- ♪ I run my mouth ♪
- Hi.

38:00.162 --> 38:03.161
♪ Like a fool ♪

38:03.161 --> 38:04.675
Coming home?

38:04.922 --> 38:06.255
Yeah.

38:06.998 --> 38:08.864
Okay.

38:11.039 --> 38:15.258
♪ I'll be so quiet for you ♪

38:18.759 --> 38:23.128
♪ Look like a child for you ♪

38:24.734 --> 38:26.601
- Hey.
- Hi.

38:26.727 --> 38:29.645
♪ Be like a shadow of a shadow of the... ♪

38:29.646 --> 38:32.842
- Oh, a... dandelion.
- Mm-hmm.

38:32.843 --> 38:34.593
Gee, thanks.

38:35.241 --> 38:37.963
Could have at least stolen
some peonies from the set.

38:37.964 --> 38:39.164
[Laughs]

38:40.259 --> 38:42.680
Tonight was so crazy.

38:42.904 --> 38:44.303
[Sighs]

38:44.304 --> 38:48.064
This whole thing makes you
realize what's really important.

38:48.064 --> 38:50.989
♪ Babe, you let me down easy ♪

38:51.017 --> 38:55.680
- I just left my wife.
- ♪ For I have grown weary on my own ♪

38:59.445 --> 39:05.900
♪ Oh, all alone, I wander aimless ♪

39:05.901 --> 39:15.325
♪ I work the corner of an endless grid ♪

39:20.277 --> 39:24.878
♪ I'll be so still for you ♪

39:28.271 --> 39:30.888
♪ Like a dead god ♪

39:35.194 --> 39:41.006
- I'm sorry. You're not a monster.
- ♪ Wait until my eyes part ♪

39:42.437 --> 39:46.528
- ♪ Oh, all for you ♪
- Yeah, I am.

